We love bringing Pinterest dreams to life!  But make sure you have a realistic floral budget.  Your floral budget should be roughly 20% of your overall wedding budget.  Things add up so quickly, especially flowers.  I recommend focusing on larger pieces (installations, arch, bridal bouquet, tall centerpieces) that all of your guests will see and enjoy🤍
This is your reminder to order your love Valentine’s Day flowers💗💗 photographer @trishburtzel
We sell out every year.  Get on the list for 💗VALENTINE’S DAY💗
💗💗 photographer @trishburtzel

Pro Tip!  If you are having your reception in the same room as your ceremony, I highly recommend repurposing your ceremony floral/install as a backdrop for your harvest table.  Repurpose those beauties!!✨ photographer @trishburtzel
There is something extra sweet about weddings where I grow & pick the flowers myself 💗 peonies from my garden and my friend Bev’s // photographer @trishburtzel
Last few days to order VALENTINE’S DAY FLOWERS💗💗 link in bio!

We are all for saving money and utilizing it in the best way possible.  Fake flowers are actually *more* expensive than fresh in most cases.  But they give off a cheap vibe.  Don’t take shortcuts that could completely change the theme of your wedding.  Ask your florist what their recommendations are to save money and still bring your floral dreams to life.
Hurry hurry!  We sell out every year. Link in bio 💗
Vday // it’s a big deal around here🌹🌹

Sending a big hug to all the florists out there whose studio is a disaster.  Who’s swept countless number of times and yet you’re still ankle deep in foliage clippings while designing a work of art for someone who will be ecstatic to receive it.  Who’s stomped and broken down cardboard hoping just one more piece will fit in the recycle bin recycle.  Who’s spent the extra minute to hand write that special love note.  Who’s skipped meals because you are designing on a deadline hoping you finish before the delivery van comes back to grab the next load.  As you’re hustling and grinding, just remember you are doing something amazing and you are making a difference ❤️💗❤️
Happy Valentine’s Day! Thank you to everyone who placed an order, we love surprising your loves💗

It’s wedding season and we are in the thick of it.  A lot of hard work goes into bringing floral dreams to life.  Hauling boxes of flowers that need to be processed, de-thorning thousands of roses, polishing candles, cutting chicken wire to form mechanics, designing on tight deadlines, working against insane heat and keeping flowers alive, delivering & setting up, ensuring every stem is in its place, cleanup, and repeat to execute the next beautiful event!  But we love it and this is what we live for🥰 Giving all of the florist out there a big hug!! You all are AMAZING!!!
Oh Juliet, how I love you 🍑🍑
We are LOVING all the color this year!!

EXCITING NEWS!! I am so excited to share that WE ARE MOVING!! At the end of wedding season.  Our new location will be in Andover, MN.  Found a little slice of Heaven in the woods (but not too far out for weddings), privacy, land to grow gardens, maybe build a little polebarn for the biz, dogs to roam, it’s perfect.  After much prayer and trust in God, He opened doors and made this happen in the middle of wedding season!! It’s been a busy month to day the least and I’ve been challenged beyond what I thought I couldn’t do.  God is so good!! 

So, with that, we are having a STUDIO SALE!  I have too much stuff to move and want to find good homes for everything.  So, COME OVER, please.  This coming Monday 9/25, Tuesday 9/26, and Wednesday 9/27.  Shop our vases, candles, candlesticks, ribbons, installs, floral supplies, and more!

A HUGE thank you to my mom for keeping me going, helping me every day with home renos, cleaning, painting, helping me with the biz, and just her unconditional love.  Ilysm🤍

THANK YOU to our incredible couples, friends, and family who trust us to bring their floral dreams to life and everyone who has supported us over the years.  Because of you all, you have afforded us this opportunity.  From the bottom of my heart, thank you!!🥰🥰
